claim.claim-text:
A power tool comprising:
a housing;
an output shaft extending from the housing in a direction of a tool axis;
a motion sensor configured to sense motion of the tool housing;
a control circuit configured to receive an input signal from the motion sensor, to make a first determination, based on the input signal, whether the tool is being operated in a horizontal mode or a vertical mode, and to make a second determination, based on the input signal, whether the tool axis is substantially level when the tool is being operated in the horizontal mode or the tool axis is substantially plumb when the tool is being operated in the vertical mode, and
an indicator coupled to the control circuit, the indicator configured to receive an output signal from the control circuit that causes the indicator to indicate whether the tool axis is level when being operated in the horizontal mode or plumb when being operated in the vertical mode.
